overview.longBusinessSummary: OneSpaWorld Holdings Limited operates health and wellness centers onboard cruise ships and at destination resorts in the United States and internationally. Its health and wellness centers offer services, such as body care, salon, and skin care services and products; fitness facilities, specialized fitness classes, and personal fitness training; pain management, including acupuncture and light therapies; body composition analytics and weight loss, systemic detoxification, and nutrition regimens; and medi-spa services comprising dermal fillers, skin tightening, weight reduction, and IV therapies, as well as massage and facial treatment, hair styling, manicure and pedicure, microneedling, cupping, posture, gait analysis, nutritional/weight management and dietary consultations, nutrition coaching, yoga, meditation, biofeedback, teeth whitening, and mindfulness services. The company also sells health and wellness, fitness, and beauty related products, including facial skincare, body care, and orthotics and detox supplements through its timetospa.com website. In addition, it provides its guests access to beauty and wellness brands, including ELEMIS, Grown Alchemist, Krastase, Dysport, Restylane, Thermage, CoolSculpting, truSculpt 3D, truSculpt iD, Good Feet, Lightstim, and Hyperice with various brands offered in the cruise market. OneSpaWorld Holdings Limited was founded in 2017 and is headquartered in Nassau, Bahamas.
